creator: Various
description:
LibriVox recording of Short Poetry Collection 144 by Various.
Read in English by Librivox Volunteers
This is a collection of 24 poems read by LibriVox volunteers for May 2015. This collection includes the following: Charge of the Light Brigade, by Alfred, Lord Tennyson Circe, by Augusta Webster Desert Pools, by Sara Teasdale In the Early Pearly Morning: Song by Valgovind, by Laurence Hope Epitaph, by Samuel Taylor Coleridge The Eternal Justice, by Anne Reeve Aldrich Gingo Biloba - Splitting Up, by Johann Wolfgang von Goethe The Glory of the Day Was in her Face, by James Weldon Johnson The Great Mercy, by Katharine Tynan Hinkson Introduction to Songs of Innocence, by William Blake I Was Looking a Long While, by Walt Whitman Joy, by Sara Teasdale The Lamb, by William Blake Longing, by Matthew Arnold Miracles, by Walt Whitman Ode to Work in Springtime, by Thomas Ybarra Out of the Morning, by Emily Dickinson Paul Revere’s Ride, by Henry Wadsworth Longfellow Remember, by Christina Rossetti Romance, by Claude McKay Saint Peter, by Henry Lawson Solitude, by Harold Monro Sonnet 147, by William Shakespeare Stonewall Jackson's Way, by John Williamson Palmer The Sun Used to Shine, by Edward Thomas Thistledown, by Harold Monro Thought, by Walt Whitman Thursday, by Edna St. Vincent Millay To Daffodils, by Robert Herrick Unknown Country, by Harold Monro Wind of Summer, by Michael Field For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
